"{\"uid\": \"horseandhound.co.uk-news-olympics-cross-country-laura-collett-2024-865894\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Laura CollettandLondon 52were simply sensational during theirParis Olympicscross-country round.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 95, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As second team member for Great Britain, Laura and the 15-year-old she co-owns with Keith Scott and Karen Bartlett put in an almost faultless round on day two of theOlympic eventingcompetition.\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8856271346731128, \"rank\": 0.11979004448853724, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 137, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 180, \"end\": 191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\", \"score\": 0.5297979123518304, \"rank\": 0.7754100477849662, \"text\": \"Keith Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 196, \"end\": 201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\", \"score\": 0.9963195074580775, \"rank\": 0.0033815826023185233, \"text\": \"Karen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura and London finished two seconds over the 9min 2sec optimum time, picking up .8 of a time-fault to now sit on 18.3.\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means that shouldMichael Jungand Chipmunk FRH jump clear inside the time later this afternoon, Laura will be demoted from herdressage leadinto second as Michaelcurrently has a score of 17.8after the first phase.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 512, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was amazing and London is just my horse of a lifetime,\\\" said an emotional Laura.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's just incredible.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not really believe we have just done that, to be honest.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just relieved that it's over and I have not let anyone down.\\\"\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura said that the crowds were \\\"unbelievable\\\" and that it was a \\\"buzz from start to finish\\\".\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 34-year-old rider, who won team gold on London 52 at the Tokyo Olympics has produced this gelding since he was a young horse.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think for me, knowing what he was like as a young horse and knowing how much he's had to trust me and believe in me - he's not a natural cross-country horse and then he goes around a course like that on railway tracks, so it just shows what a partnership you can build up and you can make them believe in you,\\\" she explained.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have full faith in him now, which means I can go and enjoy myself out there.\\\"\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura said that the optimum tight is \\\"tight\\\" but that London 52 losing a front shoe early on course did not help her to finish inside the time.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are a couple of places where you can really let them gallop, but there are an awful lot of twists and turns and after he lost a shoe, he was slipping all over the place.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That meant I had to be quite careful on those turns and really kill the speed to get around the trees without doing anything stupid like slipping over.\\\"\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of London's lost shoe, Laura stated: \\\"Fingers crossed the team will get him sorted tonight and yes, it's not not ideal, but it just shows what a good horse he is.\\\"\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the Pierre Le Goupil-designed Olympic cross-country track, Laura said it had provoked a lot of \\\"head scratching\\\".\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2224, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To be honest, up until this morning I was planning to jump the right hand corner coming out of the second water [at fence 10 - The Vauban Citadel], but I watched a few jump it and it looked like the striding to the left corner was just a bit easier and more obvious for the horses so I changed my mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 2280, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura also said her plan as always to go off the left-hand side drop at the influential fence 16abcd, The Viewpoint over the Grand Canal.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2586, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was always very much wanting to jump left off the drop - I just felt like the ditch was a bit of a nothing ditch and there were too many unknown circumstances there for how horses would read it and jump it with only two strides to the triple brush out.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just thought that was an unnecessary risk, so for me that was always plan A and stuck to it and it rode really nicely.\\\"\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura's phenomenal two-phase score, paired with British pathfinderTom McEwen's clear round inside the timewith JL Dublin means that after the second rotation of team riders, the British team has a commanding lead over the rest of the field with France in second and Japan in third.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3104, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9961206140711626, \"rank\": 0.002410643412998051, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.138869758218377e-16, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}, {\"begin\": 3215, \"end\": 3217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\", \"score\": 0.9999995080007766, \"rank\": 4.919996433828222e-07, \"text\": \"JL\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\"}, {\"begin\": 3218, \"end\": 3224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9831079865193744, \"rank\": 0.017182193250208415, \"text\": \"Dublin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_GAA\"}, {\"begin\": 3282, \"end\": 3289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9961206140711626, \"rank\": 0.002410643412998051, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3349, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7821760638910448, \"rank\": 0.18448565225461128, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"End of day update:Laura Collett and London 52 now sit in second after Michael Jung and Chipmunk jumped clear inside the time, which promoted the German to top spot.\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3405, \"end\": 3418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\", \"score\": 0.9988531015029164, \"rank\": 0.001148203587